\begin_layout Enumerate
Are the preferences represented by this particular linear utility function
 strongly monotonic? No.
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $u(x_{1}+\epsilon,x_{2})=a(x_{1}+\epsilon)-x_{2}>ax_{1}-x_{2}=u(x_{1},x_{2})$
\end_inset

, which means that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[{x_{1}+\epsilon\atop x_{2}}\right]\succ\left[{x_{1}\atop x_{2}}\right]$
\end_inset

.
 However, note also that 
\begin_inset Formula $u(x_{1},x_{2}+\epsilon)=ax_{1}-x_{2}-\epsilon<ax_{1}-x_{2}=u(x_{1},x_{2}),$
\end_inset

 which means that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[{x_{1}\atop x_{2}}\right]\succ\left[{x_{1}\atop x_{2}+\epsilon}\right]$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

